latestIgtvVideos.title: ‘Nadi’
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Posted @withregram • @newkaryshma Enjoy our first music video of “Nadi" from our album, “Someday”! "Nadi" is an old folk song from Karyshma's 2020 album "Someday". The song represents a South Asian musical tradition called Thumri that dates back to the 15th century and is connected with eroticism and evocative love. These folk songs have survived for generations thanks to the courtesans who kept singing them and handing them down to the next generation.
Karyshma's fresh take on this folk song lives somewhere between Lubbock, Texas and Lucknow, India, braiding the strands of American country guitar riffs with North India's folk. 

The song is about a woman swinging on a swing by the riverside. With her body flowing back and forth, she misses her beloved.

Because Things don’t happen to you they happen for you.
